<TITLE> Train links to northern region snapped </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 13 (bdnews24.com)  Train links between Dhaka and northern Bangladesh snapped Thursday as the Rajshahi-bound Silk City Express train derailed in the evening on the east side of the Jamuna bridge in Bhuapur upazila in Tangail. The Dhaka-bound Lalmonirhat Express was stranded on the west side of the Jamuna bridge because of the accident. Additional director general of Bangladesh Railway Asadullah told bdnews24.com that the engine of the Rajshahi-bound train ran off the track at about 5.50pm. He said a relief train from Dhaka left for the accident site at about 7.50pm and the rescue operation would start once the train reached there. He hoped rescue operations would be complete by midnight. Officer-in-charge of Jamuna bridge East Police Station Mostafa Monzur Mahmud said at 8:30pm that Silk City Express was going from Joydevpur to Rajshahi. The engine and a compartment of the train derailed when it reached Char Patalkandi area in Bhuapur upazila. He said the Padma Express, coming to Dhaka from Rajshahi, also got stranded at Sadanandapur station in Sirajganj. Mahmud said police had been deployed in the area for security of the passengers. bdnews24.c
